WEBVTT

00:00.162 --> 00:00.622
How are you?

00:01.964 --> 00:02.825
Good to see you awake.

00:02.845 --> 00:03.185
You're good.

00:03.365 --> 00:03.706
You're here.

00:03.906 --> 00:04.587
All of our campuses.

00:04.647 --> 00:05.267
Glad you're here.

00:05.868 --> 00:07.850
Welcome to subscribe week number four.

00:07.950 --> 00:08.270
Wow.

00:08.390 --> 00:08.951
Time flies.

00:09.512 --> 00:10.433
My name is Brian Vassel.

00:10.453 --> 00:13.896
I'm one of your pastors and it is my absolute honor to be here with you.

00:14.096 --> 00:15.277
Want to welcome all of our campuses.

00:15.317 --> 00:16.619
Those attending online as well.

00:16.959 --> 00:17.580
Glad you're here.

00:17.820 --> 00:22.305
If you would take out those notes you receive when you came in today, I want to encourage you to write some stuff down.

00:22.325 --> 00:25.027
I want to give you something that you didn't have when you came in.

00:25.067 --> 00:27.570
That's our goal each and every week.

00:27.682 --> 00:30.385
If you missed last week, make sure you go back on our app and pick it up.

00:30.445 --> 00:37.553
It was Pastor Tyler and his brother Carson came out and just absolutely did a great job talking about personal growth, one of our ethos.

00:37.593 --> 00:41.417
We're talking about the values that make potential church, potential church.

00:41.437 --> 00:44.521
And it's our prayer that you can subscribe to these values.

00:44.541 --> 00:49.206
These are some things you can put into your own life and value what we value here as a church.

00:49.426 --> 00:53.551
I want to also remind you don't forget July 24th of the 27th is youth camp.

00:53.591 --> 00:56.274
Now, youth camp is exciting.

00:56.418 --> 01:01.425
I can tell you that because my daughter has gone so many years in a row and it has honestly changed her life.

01:02.426 --> 01:08.435
It is one of those things that when you get here amongst your peers and you have fun and learn and something changes in the heart.

01:09.236 --> 01:22.514
And if you have a young person and you've been battling them at home or you have a young person, you want somebody to reinforce the values of Christ in their life, I would encourage you, implore you even, don't miss the opportunity to put them in a place where they're not only going to have fun and grow and learn, but really

01:22.658 --> 01:24.581
get closer to Christ in the process.

01:24.601 --> 01:26.103
So that's my heart for youth camp.

01:26.163 --> 01:26.844
I absolutely love it.

01:27.405 --> 01:29.408
And I'm looking forward to being a small part of it.

01:29.428 --> 01:30.390
It's exciting.

01:30.430 --> 01:34.175
I feel like the gray hair, I can't hide amongst the students anymore.

01:34.295 --> 01:37.220
It prohibits me, but I love to be able to be a part of it.

01:37.240 --> 01:39.243
Today we're talking about something near and dear to my heart.

01:39.263 --> 01:40.405
You probably already know what that is.

01:40.445 --> 01:41.406
You see it on your outline.

01:41.647 --> 01:43.409
We're going to talk today about honor.

01:44.070 --> 01:47.776
Honor is something that a lot of us think we understand.

01:47.836 --> 01:49.298
We have a pretty good grip on it.

01:49.378 --> 01:52.201
We're pretty sure we get it, but let me ask you this question.

01:52.221 --> 01:55.566
Anybody in the room today, any of our campuses, how many of you like to be honored?

01:55.606 --> 01:56.246
Raise your hand.

01:57.107 --> 01:57.548
Be honest.

01:58.349 --> 02:00.171
Come on, every hand ship, you love it, right?

02:00.652 --> 02:01.373
You look great today.

02:01.393 --> 02:02.334
Did I take you guys look good?

02:03.215 --> 02:05.958
That whole section back there especially, you guys look fantastic.

02:05.978 --> 02:08.361
Hallendale Beach, you guys look amazing as well.

02:08.481 --> 02:09.663
We all like to be honored, right?

02:09.683 --> 02:12.807
We all like to just sit and just be admired.

02:13.007 --> 02:15.230
Just kind of relax a little bit.

02:15.570 --> 02:16.171
No wait a second.

02:16.191 --> 02:18.834
This is my birthday weekend, so I'm going to add a little flair.

02:19.522 --> 02:20.163
I'm going to wear this.

02:21.244 --> 02:22.185
I mean, it seems to fit, right?

02:22.985 --> 02:23.486
We love.

02:23.686 --> 02:25.368
Can I get some appropriate lighting for me, please?

02:28.631 --> 02:29.252
Ah, that's better.

02:32.555 --> 02:33.516
Yeah, just soaking it in.

02:33.556 --> 02:34.397
Yeah, bring it on.

02:34.417 --> 02:34.757
I love it.

02:35.638 --> 02:36.319
More louder.

02:36.459 --> 02:36.739
Yeah.

02:39.622 --> 02:42.425
That is a pathetic display for me.

02:42.465 --> 02:43.846
I apologize to you for this.

02:44.467 --> 02:45.928
But you know, when it's your birthday, it's kind of cool.

02:45.948 --> 02:47.570
You get Facebook messages and

02:47.810 --> 02:51.135
People sing to you, and they make you brownies, and they love on you, and it's wonderful.

02:52.237 --> 02:54.761
Honor being treated well is something special.

02:54.801 --> 02:58.907
Now, this is kind of ridiculous, but man, a lot of us want to feel just like this.

03:00.390 --> 03:01.431
We want to be honored all the time.

03:01.612 --> 03:03.635
Now, is honor simply just complimenting somebody?

03:03.655 --> 03:05.197
We can bring the regular lights back up.

03:05.298 --> 03:09.985
Is honor just complimenting somebody and making them feel good, or is there something deeper to it than that?

03:10.806 --> 03:14.532
Are we doing a good job honoring each other and people in our lives?

03:14.692 --> 03:15.794
I think it's important

03:16.098 --> 03:18.421
As we discussed, we have to define kind of what honor is.

03:18.461 --> 03:19.822
And here's what it is to potential church.

03:20.042 --> 03:21.224
This comes right from our website.

03:21.244 --> 03:22.665
This is right from our ethos statement.

03:23.026 --> 03:28.231
It says this, honor is a showing of respect, giving value to and caring for.

03:28.291 --> 03:29.413
Now there's some key words in there.

03:29.433 --> 03:30.734
I want you to circle them if you would.

03:31.415 --> 03:32.736
Respect, please circle that one.

03:33.577 --> 03:35.359
Value and caring.

03:36.040 --> 03:37.822
We're going to talk a lot about those three things.

03:37.862 --> 03:41.746
Now in Hebrew, the word kabod, it's translated to give weight to.

03:42.210 --> 03:54.029
When you read the word kabod and scriptures, it means to give weight to or to honor, to hold in high regard, to respect, to care about and care for, to put others above ourselves.

03:54.069 --> 03:57.955
Now, we don't live in a society that tends to favor honor a whole lot, do we?

03:58.596 --> 04:03.524
I mean, how, once the last time you were walking into a store and somebody held the door open for you, it doesn't happen as much as it used to, does it?

04:04.205 --> 04:08.071
Or in traffic, you ever driving in traffic and somebody pulls up next to you and they're like, go ahead.

04:08.972 --> 04:10.034
Does that ever happen to you?

04:10.626 --> 04:12.188
It doesn't happen to me ever, right?

04:12.208 --> 04:13.049
It's always the other way around.

04:13.069 --> 04:16.554
It's like, I was here first, even if I wasn't here first, I'm going now, right?

04:17.335 --> 04:18.857
The culture struggles with honor.

04:19.738 --> 04:25.686
Whether it be honoring our boss, or honoring our spouse, or honoring our cell, what does that look like?

04:26.968 --> 04:30.052
It's almost like it's some kind of lost Jedi art.

04:30.773 --> 04:34.979
Honor was cool, respect was cool in the 1950s, but now it's just plain old fashioned.

04:35.940 --> 04:38.483
To have respect for one another just blindly?

04:39.104 --> 04:40.466
Does that even exist anymore?

04:40.834 --> 04:42.116
Maybe not.

04:43.237 --> 04:43.918
I think it should.

04:45.239 --> 04:46.020
Let me show you a picture.

04:46.161 --> 04:47.863
This picture went viral last week.

04:47.883 --> 04:48.884
Maybe you've seen it on the internet.

04:49.184 --> 04:51.207
Let's put it up on the screen.

04:51.507 --> 04:52.208
This is a great picture.

04:52.228 --> 04:58.176
If you haven't seen it, this is a guy who we don't know his name, the person who snapped the picture with somebody in traffic with him.

04:58.876 --> 04:59.577
This is a soldier.

05:00.158 --> 05:04.964
And what he's doing is he's standing out in the pouring rain, saluting a passing funeral procession.

05:06.125 --> 05:07.387
We don't know if he knew them or not.

05:07.407 --> 05:09.810
We just know that's respect.

05:10.914 --> 05:11.655
That's honor.

05:11.675 --> 05:13.436
And I want to tell you, that picture was taken last week.

05:13.456 --> 05:17.821
So I want to assure you that honor and respect are both alive and well in 2017.

05:19.242 --> 05:20.303
But that's where we need to go.

05:21.484 --> 05:22.565
That's how we need to honor.

05:22.665 --> 05:27.250
At that level of commitment, honor, and sacrifice.

05:27.310 --> 05:28.551
Why should we do it?

05:29.132 --> 05:29.592
Why honor?

05:29.612 --> 05:30.273
I'm glad you asked.

05:30.293 --> 05:31.093
It's there in your outline.

05:31.114 --> 05:32.535
I want to invite you to fill these things in.

05:32.935 --> 05:37.420
When we honor, here's a good reason, because honor reveals what's happening inside of me.

05:38.361 --> 05:39.922
Honor reveals what's happening.

05:40.450 --> 05:41.231
inside of me.

05:41.671 --> 05:42.472
Anybody know what this is?

05:42.492 --> 05:43.793
You probably don't know until I turn it on.

05:43.813 --> 05:45.215
Can we get the lights off just for a second?

05:45.435 --> 05:46.756
You'll know what it is when I flip it on.

05:47.397 --> 05:47.577
Oops.

05:48.017 --> 05:49.218
If I gotta find the button, there we go.

05:50.139 --> 05:50.800
You know what this is?

05:51.781 --> 05:53.162
It's a black light, right?

05:53.863 --> 05:56.225
I wanna challenge you to do something next time you go to stay in a hotel.

05:59.869 --> 06:02.731
Or next restaurant you go, bring one of these and shine it around your table.

06:02.912 --> 06:03.512
No, don't do that.

06:03.532 --> 06:04.713
You're gonna bring the lights back up.

06:05.634 --> 06:06.835
Why don't you wanna do that?

06:07.896 --> 06:09.618
Because it reveals stuff that's hidden.

06:10.306 --> 06:10.666
Doesn't it?

06:10.987 --> 06:13.530
It looks great on the outside, but put the black line on it, what happens?

06:13.571 --> 06:15.093
It reveals what's underneath.

06:16.455 --> 06:17.696
I think honor does that with our heart.

06:18.898 --> 06:22.423
I think honor reveals a lot about what's going on inside of us.

06:24.005 --> 06:27.290
Because when we have the opportunity to honor and we don't do it, you know what it reveals?

06:27.350 --> 06:28.531
Maybe you're struggling with pride.

06:29.913 --> 06:34.660
When we don't honor and we have the opportunity to respect someone, maybe it reveals something, maybe you feel like they're below you.

06:34.700 --> 06:35.561
You'd never tell them that.

06:36.723 --> 06:39.186
Before that black light comes on and says, something's not right in the heart.

06:40.194 --> 06:42.056
Maybe you don't see them the way God sees them.

06:42.196 --> 06:46.281
I don't know, but I know that honor reveals the condition of our heart.

06:46.982 --> 06:48.905
Here's another reason why this is in your outline as well.

06:49.285 --> 06:55.332
We honor to respect others and affirm their value, to respect others and affirm their value.

06:55.372 --> 06:56.173
Now let's have fun with this.

06:56.193 --> 06:59.698
Everybody close your eyes if you would, all of our campuses close your eyes, and here's what I want you to picture.

06:59.718 --> 07:05.304
I want you to imagine, this will be easy, the most annoying person in your life right now.

07:06.946 --> 07:09.970
If they're with you, do not squeeze their hand, do not elbow them,

07:10.338 --> 07:11.019
Do not point to them.

07:11.039 --> 07:11.380
You got them.

07:11.400 --> 07:11.981
You got their picture.

07:12.021 --> 07:12.642
You know who they are.

07:12.682 --> 07:14.484
You're like, no, we're too holy for that.

07:14.544 --> 07:15.967
Now you know who they are, right?

07:16.347 --> 07:17.028
Picture that person.

07:17.048 --> 07:17.569
They're annoying.

07:17.589 --> 07:19.272
They are the sandpaper person of your life.

07:19.492 --> 07:20.694
They annoy the tar out of you.

07:20.714 --> 07:22.957
You can't believe that you possibly put up with them.

07:23.138 --> 07:24.199
Now I want you to think about this way.

07:24.219 --> 07:25.601
Your eyes are closed picturing their face.

07:26.963 --> 07:27.765
Listen to the statement.

07:28.886 --> 07:32.772
God loves that person as much as he loves you.

07:35.276 --> 07:39.122
God loves that annoying person in your life as much as he loves you.

07:40.674 --> 07:41.375
You can open your eyes.

07:41.415 --> 07:44.859
Don't fall asleep on me.

07:44.879 --> 07:47.642
Now that sounds, of course he does, but we don't treat each other like that.

07:48.984 --> 07:51.607
The annoying ones don't deserve my honor or my respect.

07:53.269 --> 07:56.973
But God says, but I love them as much as I love you.

07:58.395 --> 08:01.198
And I think we start treating people with honor intentionally.

08:02.099 --> 08:04.242
We start to see them the way God sees them.

08:05.058 --> 08:12.889
every single person on this earth, in this building, in all of our campuses and around the world, every single one, if you have a pulse and a heartbeat, guess what?

08:13.149 --> 08:13.910
You matter to God.

08:16.093 --> 08:18.977
God knows your name and you're important.

08:21.100 --> 08:25.266
We gotta see people the way God sees them, not the way we want to see them.

08:26.287 --> 08:30.293
And it doesn't require us to be in complete, to be the best buddies either.

08:30.333 --> 08:33.938
In fact, I put in your notes this way, honor doesn't require agreement.

08:34.850 --> 08:36.172
Honor doesn't require agreement.

08:36.372 --> 08:38.355
I don't have to agree with you to respect you.

08:39.717 --> 08:42.100
I don't have to have the same exact viewpoints to honor you.

08:42.661 --> 08:43.562
Why should I honor you?

08:43.642 --> 08:47.207
Because God created you special with gifts and abilities and talents.

08:48.068 --> 08:49.730
And He loves you just as much as He loves me.

08:51.172 --> 08:54.496
We can agree hard to heart without seeing eye to eye.

08:55.338 --> 09:00.304
We don't have to be completely lined up for me to pay you respect.

09:00.485 --> 09:01.586
Everybody matters.

09:01.666 --> 09:03.328
Honor reveals what's going on in our heart.

09:03.388 --> 09:05.750
It also affirms people and reminds them of their value.

09:05.770 --> 09:07.151
Now, who am I supposed to honor?

09:07.171 --> 09:08.112
I'm glad you asked that again.

09:08.332 --> 09:08.713
Here we go.

09:08.753 --> 09:09.373
Here's number one.

09:09.594 --> 09:11.195
We need to honor first and foremost.

09:11.215 --> 09:12.056
You can probably guess it.

09:12.536 --> 09:12.837
God.

09:14.298 --> 09:15.359
We need to honor God.

09:15.399 --> 09:17.221
Now, how do we honor and respect God?

09:17.241 --> 09:19.103
Well, I put some things down on your list.

09:19.303 --> 09:21.045
Let's look at this verse first from Psalm 22.

09:21.065 --> 09:23.487
It says, Praise the Lord.

09:23.827 --> 09:24.648
All who fear Him.

09:25.008 --> 09:25.849
Talking about God there.

09:26.470 --> 09:27.190
Look at the next phrase.

09:27.210 --> 09:27.711
What does it say?

09:28.952 --> 09:30.253
Let's try that like we mean it, okay?

09:30.273 --> 09:30.994
What does it say?

09:31.362 --> 09:32.183
Honor him, right?

09:32.303 --> 09:37.592
Honor God, all you descendants of Jacob, show him reverence, all you descendants of Israel.

09:38.633 --> 09:42.840
Scripture says, all honor starts with the way we treat and respect and honor God.

09:44.162 --> 09:45.364
God is to be honored.

09:46.526 --> 09:47.027
How do we do it?

09:47.868 --> 09:49.250
Well, we start by honoring His house.

09:50.232 --> 09:51.674
His house, of course, is the local church.

09:51.754 --> 09:53.216
We honor this house.

09:53.777 --> 09:54.398
How do we do that?

09:55.139 --> 09:58.785
I think first and foremost, this is a regular attendance.

09:58.805 --> 09:59.346
Be here.

09:59.618 --> 10:04.343
So many people I talk to are like pastor, I just can't fit church in my schedule.

10:04.363 --> 10:07.326
Well, I would suggest to you that you put church first and then fit other things around it.

10:08.247 --> 10:10.850
Because here's what happens when you don't show up on a week and you miss something.

10:11.110 --> 10:15.495
That could have been the week that from our pastor, he could have given you the answer you've been searching for for a decade.

10:17.096 --> 10:17.597
And you miss it.

10:18.538 --> 10:22.102
Or you miss the interactions in the lobby or you miss a friendship that could have possibly been.

10:22.122 --> 10:23.643
It's important to be here regularly.

10:24.464 --> 10:25.285
I know things come up.

10:25.846 --> 10:26.226
I do.

10:26.978 --> 10:27.999
But be here as often as you can.

10:28.039 --> 10:29.000
Same thing with generosity.

10:29.020 --> 10:30.462
I listed that in your outline as well.

10:30.482 --> 10:33.486
We get nudged by God to be generous with our resources.

10:33.526 --> 10:36.129
And he's telling us, hey, I want you to respond with a tie.

10:36.149 --> 10:39.993
Then I want you to be obedient by giving a tenth of your resources back to me, which I've blessed you with.

10:40.173 --> 10:42.376
And we get that nudge and we're like, nah, you know what God?

10:43.597 --> 10:44.538
Just not feeling it today.

10:45.620 --> 10:47.442
What if you don't do what you say you're gonna do?

10:48.843 --> 10:51.206
Regular generosity honors God.

10:51.506 --> 10:54.610
Regular attendance honors God.

10:55.714 --> 10:57.095
I put the second way we can honor God.

10:58.016 --> 10:59.418
His house is church leadership.

10:59.458 --> 11:00.719
It's to honor church leadership.

11:01.240 --> 11:04.583
1 Timothy 517, if you have your Bible as you can turn there, but I'm gonna read it to you.

11:04.603 --> 11:05.504
It's not in your outline.

11:05.884 --> 11:06.765
But listen to this verse.

11:07.566 --> 11:08.106
I like this one.

11:08.126 --> 11:10.008
You're gonna find out why in a second.

11:10.028 --> 11:18.137
The elders who direct the affairs of the church well are worthy of double honor, especially those who work, whose work is preaching and teaching.

11:18.177 --> 11:19.278
Now it seems a little self-serving.

11:19.298 --> 11:20.599
Like why would I breed that one to you?

11:20.639 --> 11:23.602
Like the people who are preaching teach deserve double honor.

11:25.122 --> 11:26.243
I'm gonna go sit here on the throne again.

11:28.125 --> 11:29.347
Yes, double honor me.

11:29.787 --> 11:31.148
That's not what Scripture's saying.

11:32.029 --> 11:33.231
You don't worship your pastors.

11:34.152 --> 11:34.973
That's not what it says.

11:35.693 --> 11:37.535
What double honor means is pray for us.

11:37.695 --> 11:39.097
Pray for spiritual leadership here.

11:40.218 --> 11:43.201
Defend their reputation when some people wanna talk bad about them.

11:44.423 --> 11:46.885
Check on them, care, give, all these kinds of things.

11:46.925 --> 11:49.288
This is a way to show double honor to the leaders of the church.

11:49.528 --> 11:51.250
Again, I did not write this verse.

11:53.058 --> 11:54.960
God said, if you want to honor me, you honor my house.

11:55.000 --> 11:57.062
The way you can honor my house is to honor my leadership.

11:58.824 --> 12:01.146
Don't gossip when people around you are gossiping about stuff.

12:02.868 --> 12:04.910
Defend this place, defend your spiritual leader.

12:04.930 --> 12:07.653
That's the way we can double honor God's leaders.

12:07.673 --> 12:08.173
Here's the third.

12:09.014 --> 12:09.995
Respect and reverence.

12:10.636 --> 12:11.396
Leviticus 1930.

12:11.456 --> 12:12.517
These are references there.

12:12.537 --> 12:17.242
I don't have time to read all of them, but if you want to kind of go back and see where I got these from, that's where those verses come from.

12:18.083 --> 12:21.106
This is respect for God's house, for example, being here on time.

12:22.882 --> 12:24.384
Arriving for services on time.

12:24.424 --> 12:28.530
Now, I know that things happen and people arrive late, but when we arrive late, what happens?

12:28.550 --> 12:30.573
We walk into a row where people are already worshiping.

12:31.995 --> 12:32.656
Or how about this one?

12:32.676 --> 12:39.545
Maybe not saying nobody in this group does this or our campuses, but some people actually leave before it's over.

12:39.665 --> 12:40.106
Did you know that?

12:41.828 --> 12:42.129
They do.

12:42.169 --> 12:43.150
They leave early.

12:43.671 --> 12:45.273
Well, I've got what I needed, so I'm going.

12:45.293 --> 12:49.118
And what happens when they do that is they get up and they disturb the entire row of people they're sitting next to.

12:50.901 --> 12:51.762
And they're trying to worship.

12:53.154 --> 12:54.115
That's not honoring the house.

12:55.898 --> 12:58.562
That means I want to get out and beat the traffic.

12:58.582 --> 13:02.007
Or when they get up and they leave, they leave coffee cups and balled up pieces of paper.

13:04.591 --> 13:06.834
And I think to myself, man, I want to honor God's house.

13:07.856 --> 13:08.697
I want to treat it nice.

13:08.737 --> 13:09.839
I want to keep it clean, right?

13:10.039 --> 13:11.281
That's that honors God.

13:12.302 --> 13:13.965
Honoring his house.

13:13.985 --> 13:15.086
You've got to keep these things in mind.

13:15.126 --> 13:17.690
These behaviors absolutely matter.

13:17.850 --> 13:20.795
The way you treat the parking volunteers, did you treat them nice today when you came in?

13:21.896 --> 13:23.058
Our parking team is awesome.

13:23.490 --> 13:24.291
They're out there in the rain.

13:24.371 --> 13:25.072
We love these guys.

13:25.092 --> 13:25.672
They're amazing.

13:25.692 --> 13:26.193
They're incredible.

13:26.333 --> 13:27.034
All of our campuses.

13:29.336 --> 13:31.158
Now we applaud them until they tell us to stop.

13:33.080 --> 13:35.002
You guys come through and you're like, OK, I got a thing.

13:35.022 --> 13:37.644
You're waving the next group over and you're like, you get impatient.

13:38.045 --> 13:40.307
The way we treat each other as far as volunteers, right?

13:40.327 --> 13:41.448
We're just all serving together.

13:42.950 --> 13:46.473
How do we take care and treat people that serve in the house?

13:47.694 --> 13:49.036
All of our teams are incredible.

13:49.056 --> 13:51.378
You hand it off your child if you have children in one of our

13:51.522 --> 13:55.568
preschool rooms, to people who are gonna love on them and help them to learn about Christ.

13:57.130 --> 13:57.851
How do we treat them?

13:59.533 --> 14:04.199
So we have to have respect for the house and some behaviors we can certainly think about.

14:04.259 --> 14:07.203
Next one is, another way to honor God is by caring for his people.

14:07.264 --> 14:07.904
Please fill that in.

14:09.226 --> 14:11.970
We honor God by caring for his people.

14:12.451 --> 14:13.793
How many in the room today have children?

14:13.833 --> 14:14.974
Raise your hand, all of our campuses.

14:15.455 --> 14:16.216
How many of you guys have kids?

14:16.516 --> 14:19.220
If you don't raise your hand, it's okay, just claim them.

14:19.380 --> 14:20.722
You do, you're a parent, okay?

14:21.090 --> 14:24.695
How does it make you feel when somebody else beside you does something nice for your kid?

14:26.037 --> 14:27.118
Makes you feel pretty good, doesn't it?

14:27.719 --> 14:27.879
Right?

14:27.919 --> 14:33.106
Whether they've taken the dinner or keeping for three weeks or whatever they're going to do to, that's always nice.

14:33.146 --> 14:34.768
I miss you, I see you, right?

14:37.371 --> 14:38.253
It makes you feel good.

14:39.014 --> 14:42.418
Because not only is your child being honored, but you're kind of honored in the process, aren't you?

14:43.520 --> 14:44.281
It's a cool feeling.

14:45.001 --> 14:48.466
Now, look at this verse in Proverbs chapter 14 verse 31.

14:50.946 --> 15:02.844
Those who oppress the poor insult their maker, but helping the poor honors him, him being God, when we help the poor, when we help people that need our help, it honors God.

15:06.229 --> 15:07.411
Matthew 22 talks about it.

15:07.451 --> 15:14.061
Jesus says, when you bring a glass of cold water to someone who's thirsty, you're not just serving that person, you're serving me, Christ said.

15:16.565 --> 15:19.890
When we serve other people, we serve God's children,

15:21.314 --> 15:21.975
It honors God.

15:23.096 --> 15:24.037
It shows that we care.

15:24.478 --> 15:25.699
It's a sign of respect.

15:25.900 --> 15:27.762
We have to honor each other.

15:29.944 --> 15:33.929
It's not just an act of kindness, it's an act of worship.

15:33.949 --> 15:39.055
When you serve others, when you take care of others, it's an act of worship to God, caring for his kids.

15:41.018 --> 15:43.060
The next one in your outline is by obeying his word.

15:43.280 --> 15:45.283
Another way we can honor God is by obeying his word.

15:45.583 --> 15:46.965
Verse Samuel 15, verse 22.

15:48.407 --> 15:51.250
But Samuel replied, what is more pleasing to the Lord?

15:51.778 --> 15:55.082
Your burnt offerings and sacrifices or your obedience to his voice.

15:55.122 --> 15:55.662
Good question.

15:56.003 --> 15:58.686
Is it what we do or how we obey?

16:00.107 --> 16:00.928
Look at this next line.

16:00.948 --> 16:01.288
I love it.

16:01.649 --> 16:02.550
It's an exclamation point.

16:02.590 --> 16:04.151
Capital L says, listen.

16:05.113 --> 16:06.014
Obedience is what?

16:07.075 --> 16:07.335
Better.

16:07.475 --> 16:09.097
Underline that, circle it and start.

16:09.197 --> 16:11.219
Obedience is better than sacrifice.

16:11.520 --> 16:16.945
What we do for God, how we obey him is more important than anything else.

16:18.968 --> 16:21.170
It's like setting curfew for your kid, you know?

16:21.346 --> 16:25.212
If you have teenagers and you set curfew, let's say you said an 11 p.m. curfew.

16:25.452 --> 16:27.034
Why do you set an 11 p.m. curfew?

16:27.796 --> 16:30.339
Because you know nothing good happens after 11 p.m., right?

16:30.359 --> 16:31.381
You want them back in your house.

16:32.002 --> 16:35.567
Well, what if you set an 11 p.m. curfew and your kid comes back in at 1 a.m.?

16:37.129 --> 16:38.852
I can see people nodding their heads like, let me add them.

16:38.892 --> 16:39.613
I'm ready, right?

16:40.835 --> 16:41.316
What do you do?

16:42.197 --> 16:42.898
You're upset.

16:43.394 --> 16:47.981
because you have told somebody to be obedient and return at a certain time and they have disobeyed you.

16:48.181 --> 16:52.588
But what if they told you, by the way, mom, I know you're mad that I broke curfew, but I cleaned my room earlier today.

16:53.690 --> 16:54.672
I hope that's good enough.

16:56.174 --> 16:56.655
Does that work?

16:59.499 --> 17:01.743
No, of course it doesn't work.

17:01.763 --> 17:02.784
But we do it with God all the time.

17:02.844 --> 17:04.547
God says, I want you to gather together in church.

17:04.848 --> 17:09.755
Church, well, you know God, what I did do, I went out on my boat and I communed with nature.

17:10.216 --> 17:11.538
That's close, right?

17:12.802 --> 17:14.004
God says, pray, pray.

17:14.024 --> 17:15.626
Well, I do kind of pray.

17:15.666 --> 17:17.850
I pray for the lot of numbers that I picked to come in, right?

17:18.190 --> 17:18.731
That's close.

17:20.113 --> 17:22.898
That's not obedience.

17:22.918 --> 17:24.740
God wants us to obey.

17:24.921 --> 17:28.206
We honor Him and we follow His directions to the letter.

17:28.266 --> 17:28.506
Why?

17:28.526 --> 17:30.609
Because God knows better for us than we do.

17:32.312 --> 17:37.039
We honor Him by being obedient.

17:37.059 --> 17:38.802
Isaiah 29, verse 13.

17:39.202 --> 17:43.526
The Lord says, these people come near to me with their mouth and honor me with their lips.

17:43.667 --> 17:44.728
But where are their hearts?

17:45.629 --> 17:46.550
Far from me.

17:48.592 --> 17:49.713
God, I wanna be obedient.

17:49.873 --> 17:50.454
I really do.

17:51.715 --> 17:52.836
I wanna make church a priority.

17:52.856 --> 17:54.037
I wanna take care of other people.

17:54.077 --> 17:55.198
I wanna become a tither.

17:55.659 --> 17:57.821
My intentions are good, but I don't do it.

17:58.362 --> 17:59.843
But God, will you please bless my life?

18:01.105 --> 18:03.347
I wanna have a good marriage eventually, but we're gonna live together.

18:03.367 --> 18:04.028
I hope that's cool.

18:04.768 --> 18:06.450
God, will you bless our union?

18:06.754 --> 18:11.201
I want to have good kids, but I don't ever make them come to church, and I'll never ever make them read the Bible.

18:11.341 --> 18:11.962
Is that okay?

18:12.262 --> 18:13.804
I mean, just God, please bless my family.

18:13.965 --> 18:16.849
We're asking God to bless disobedience, and he's not going to do that.

18:19.793 --> 18:20.755
That's not honoring to him.

18:22.938 --> 18:28.105
It's one of those things that, you know, when I see that, I just wanna, I hear all the time.

18:29.107 --> 18:31.170
If I only had more time, I'd serve at the church.

18:31.971 --> 18:33.373
If I only had more money, I'd give it.

18:34.815 --> 18:36.658
This is 2017.

18:37.122 --> 18:39.785
Are we seriously supposed to do what the Bible says?

18:39.805 --> 18:41.648
I mean, I'm just keeping up with the times, right?

18:44.271 --> 18:45.513
But God, I want you to bless my life.

18:47.395 --> 18:49.518
God says, I want you to honor me by being obedient first.

18:50.699 --> 18:52.762
Then the blessings.

18:52.802 --> 18:53.983
In fact, I put in your notes this way.

18:55.105 --> 18:58.369
We honor God with our actions, not our intentions.

19:02.094 --> 19:05.458
We honor God with our actions, not our intentions.

19:07.266 --> 19:09.628
It's not what we say we're going to do for God, it's what we do.

19:11.790 --> 19:12.691
Man, that's a big statement.

19:13.472 --> 19:15.914
So we gotta honor his house, honor his people, honor his word.

19:16.215 --> 19:17.276
Now there's a whole nother big group.

19:17.296 --> 19:20.439
Now whether we've gotten God honoring down, let's look at the second group.

19:20.519 --> 19:22.441
God wants us to honor others, please fill that in.

19:23.101 --> 19:25.244
God wants us to honor others.

19:26.265 --> 19:29.968
In fact, in Matthew 22, before I think I said Matthew 22, I meant Matthew 25.

19:30.689 --> 19:35.053
Now we're in Matthew 22, when Jesus has asked, what are the two greatest commandments?

19:35.073 --> 19:35.954
Remember what they were?

19:36.354 --> 19:38.557
If you write the scriptures in Matthew 22, what does Jesus say?

19:38.577 --> 19:41.021
He says, love God first and then who else?

19:41.662 --> 19:42.203
Your neighbor.

19:42.704 --> 19:45.288
Now it doesn't mean the person sitting next to you or in the home next to you.

19:45.548 --> 19:46.510
Loving your neighbor means who?

19:46.610 --> 19:47.892
It means everybody else.

19:49.414 --> 19:50.055
It means others.

19:50.436 --> 19:52.559
Even the people that you came to mind just a few minutes ago.

19:53.140 --> 19:56.124
Because I want you to love God first and love everybody else.

19:56.144 --> 19:57.366
Now it's pretty easy to love God.

19:57.386 --> 19:58.007
I mean, he's God.

19:58.328 --> 19:59.790
But other people really God?

20:01.593 --> 20:02.514
You want me to honor them?

20:03.042 --> 20:05.404
I'm going to warn you what we're going to talk about for the next couple of minutes.

20:05.444 --> 20:06.505
It's going to be very hard to hear.

20:08.307 --> 20:09.989
Well, let's put that to the test.

20:10.249 --> 20:12.051
Here's the first group you need to honor the government.

20:14.093 --> 20:14.894
Did it get hotter in here?

20:15.094 --> 20:15.734
I said government.

20:16.735 --> 20:18.317
You're all staring me like, nope, let's read.

20:20.559 --> 20:22.901
Let's give you the blank so you don't get skittish, right?

20:23.322 --> 20:25.163
We want to honor those that are in authority over me.

20:25.944 --> 20:27.646
Honor those that are in authority over me.

20:27.686 --> 20:28.887
The first group is the government.

20:29.267 --> 20:31.890
Everyone must submit to governing authorities.

20:32.450 --> 20:34.072
For all authority comes from where?

20:34.112 --> 20:35.054
The Electoral College?

20:35.474 --> 20:35.735
No.

20:35.795 --> 20:37.337
The Constitution?

20:37.717 --> 20:37.978
No.

20:38.218 --> 20:39.921
Where does all of this power come from?

20:40.882 --> 20:41.162
God.

20:42.064 --> 20:44.747
And in those positions of authority have been placed there by who?

20:45.348 --> 20:45.689
God.

20:46.230 --> 20:47.792
God puts leadership in place.

20:47.932 --> 20:54.181
Mayors, governors, presidents.

20:54.201 --> 20:56.043
God puts them there.

20:57.806 --> 21:00.690
Whatever political party you're a part of, whatever issues you vote,

21:01.986 --> 21:08.136
God says directly, if you want to honor, you want to learn how to be respectful, we need to honor the people that God has put in it power.

21:08.917 --> 21:09.418
Pray for them.

21:10.439 --> 21:11.721
Even if you don't agree with them, pray for them.

21:11.882 --> 21:13.945
And don't pray that they would be removed from office.

21:13.965 --> 21:16.790
That's not the prayer I'm talking about, okay?

21:16.810 --> 21:19.754
Pray that they would do well.

21:19.935 --> 21:20.195
Why?

21:20.295 --> 21:24.762
Because you live in their state, because you live in their country, because you're a part of their city.

21:24.943 --> 21:27.346
Why would you pray against a mayor if you're living the city?

21:28.929 --> 21:29.650
Support them.

21:30.178 --> 21:30.759
Honor them.

21:30.819 --> 21:33.461
Again, it's not because they deserve it or have earned it.

21:33.481 --> 21:34.242
It's because you know what?

21:34.282 --> 21:35.804
God loves them as much as He loves you.

21:36.044 --> 21:38.166
God died for them just like He died for you.

21:38.927 --> 21:40.729
Honor the government.

21:40.749 --> 21:41.329
Here's the next one.

21:41.349 --> 21:41.970
They don't get easier.

21:42.631 --> 21:43.371
Honor your boss.

21:44.813 --> 21:47.596
How many of you work for a boss that's loving, benevolent, and kind?

21:47.616 --> 21:48.056
Raise your hand.

21:48.256 --> 21:48.977
All of our campuses.

21:49.577 --> 21:49.778
Good.

21:49.878 --> 21:50.198
A few.

21:50.498 --> 21:51.019
Put your hands down.

21:51.039 --> 21:58.066
Now, the rest of you are either unemployed or your boss may not fit that description.

21:59.138 --> 22:01.662
So the Scripture say I have to honor my boss.

22:01.702 --> 22:03.425
Remember the black light check on our hearts.

22:04.987 --> 22:06.931
Servants obey your boss, Ephesians 6 says.

22:07.411 --> 22:10.577
Respect him with all your heart and try to please him as you would who?

22:11.518 --> 22:16.005
Christ, work for him or her as if you were working for Jesus himself.

22:18.229 --> 22:18.610
Really?

22:20.553 --> 22:21.134
My boss?

22:22.396 --> 22:24.319
The company I work seriously?

22:25.401 --> 22:26.322
Am I supposed, yes.

22:27.490 --> 22:31.395
We have to learn to honor people in that position of authority over us.

22:31.435 --> 22:33.617
I'm not saying do anything illegal, all right?

22:34.158 --> 22:38.443
I am saying if they ask you to work hard, you work hard to honor them, just as if you were working hard for Christ.

22:39.585 --> 22:42.709
Like he is your ultimate boss.

22:42.769 --> 22:49.156
I mean honor, not side eye, not subtweets, not pictures on Instagram or your Facebook page, little memes about your boss.

22:49.377 --> 22:50.138
Don't post that stuff.

22:50.158 --> 22:50.778
Be honorable.

22:51.720 --> 22:53.682
Be respectful to him or her.

22:54.914 --> 22:56.757
It's really, it's any authority, seriously.

22:56.797 --> 22:59.261
If you're an athlete, be honorable to you, honor your coach.

23:00.282 --> 23:01.885
If you're a student, honor your teacher.

23:01.905 --> 23:06.532
I mean, whoever's been placed in authority over you, respect and honor them.

23:06.732 --> 23:07.333
Here's the next one.

23:07.533 --> 23:09.436
We need to honor those that are in the family with me.

23:10.658 --> 23:14.204
Honor those in the family with me, starting with, and you guessed it, honoring your parents.

23:14.945 --> 23:18.530
Exodus 2012, one of the big 10 commandments says this.

23:18.711 --> 23:19.452
Honor your what?

23:19.672 --> 23:20.914
Your father and your mother.

23:21.346 --> 23:24.630
Then you will live a long, full life in the land the Lord your God is giving you.

23:24.670 --> 23:25.211
I love this.

23:26.433 --> 23:27.394
Honor your mom and dad.

23:28.235 --> 23:31.980
If you live under their roof, you need to honor and respect their wishes.

23:33.502 --> 23:34.223
I'm gonna say that again.

23:35.004 --> 23:38.168
If you live under their roof, you need to honor and respect their wishes.

23:38.348 --> 23:40.050
That doesn't just count for children this high.

23:40.291 --> 23:46.138
If you're an adult living at home, no matter what age you are, and it's their home, you need to honor and respect their wishes.

23:47.400 --> 23:49.202
That's the way this thing works.

23:50.050 --> 23:52.894
That is honorable because God has given you those parents.

23:52.914 --> 23:54.036
Now, I want to say this to you also.

23:54.076 --> 23:56.280
This goes for their whole life.

23:56.440 --> 23:57.722
Honor your parents as long as they live.

23:57.762 --> 23:58.884
Take care of your parents.

24:01.287 --> 24:02.750
Provide for them, protect them.

24:03.851 --> 24:05.554
Get them the help they need, the medical care.

24:05.574 --> 24:06.095
Love them.

24:06.716 --> 24:09.119
That is our responsibility as the children of the home.

24:09.159 --> 24:10.762
Now, let's flip that around.

24:10.822 --> 24:12.705
Parents need to honor their kids too.

24:13.306 --> 24:13.927
And I'll tell you how.

24:13.967 --> 24:16.050
The Bible tells us that parents should never

24:16.738 --> 24:19.622
provoke their children, never get them warped up and push them too hard.

24:19.902 --> 24:21.745
But sometimes we get this mixed up.

24:22.486 --> 24:25.010
Because sometimes parents hear this and they start worshiping their children.

24:27.533 --> 24:31.319
Children are not meant to be worshiped, they're not meant to be put over your spouse, they're not meant to be put over God.

24:32.580 --> 24:34.123
They're arrows you fire out into the world.

24:35.264 --> 24:38.689
Honor them and they need to honor you in return.

24:39.010 --> 24:41.253
Parents, that's an important, important, important thing.

24:41.633 --> 24:42.535
Next one, here you go.

24:42.555 --> 24:43.356
I told you they don't get easy.

24:43.836 --> 24:44.978
Honor your spouse.

24:46.018 --> 24:46.839
If you're married.

24:47.000 --> 24:48.662
Every time I say that out loud, people laugh.

24:49.303 --> 24:51.667
I always get a chuckle or two like, you don't know who I'm married to.

24:51.707 --> 24:52.148
Let's read it.

24:53.349 --> 24:53.810
Let's read it.

24:54.531 --> 24:55.272
First Peter three.

24:56.594 --> 24:59.279
Speaking to husbands here, it says, be good wives to your husband.

24:59.359 --> 25:00.180
Excuse me, to wives.

25:00.360 --> 25:02.484
Be good wives to your husbands responding to their needs.

25:03.044 --> 25:03.665
Then verse seven.

25:03.886 --> 25:05.148
The same goes for you husbands.

25:05.608 --> 25:07.291
Be good husbands to your wives.

25:07.812 --> 25:10.336
Honor them and delight in them.

25:12.139 --> 25:14.322
Honor the person that you married.

25:15.586 --> 25:17.730
honor the vows you took to them.

25:18.251 --> 25:22.518
Now, if you're in a situation where you're being abused, I'm not saying put up with that.

25:22.879 --> 25:23.420
Hear my heart.

25:25.022 --> 25:25.864
Get the help you need.

25:27.707 --> 25:33.938
All I'm saying is if a situation in your family is that you're married and there's constant conflict, you need to honor your spouse.

25:34.402 --> 25:39.569
the way you communicate to one another, the way you deal with money, the way you raise your kids, honor and respect each other.

25:39.730 --> 25:41.352
Now here's the problem with the situation.

25:41.692 --> 25:45.738
Most of us wait for the spouse, the other spouse, to respect us first.

25:46.659 --> 25:49.323
When they start treating me right, then I might start treating them right.

25:49.864 --> 25:50.285
Wrong.

25:52.047 --> 25:53.269
That's not the way this works.

25:54.671 --> 26:00.059
Scripture tells us to respect and honor first, even if they don't do it.

26:01.481 --> 26:02.482
That doesn't seem fair.

26:04.162 --> 26:05.163
They're gonna treat me like a doormat.

26:05.183 --> 26:06.184
They're gonna take advantage of me.

26:06.204 --> 26:07.986
Maybe at first, but you know what else the Scripture tells us?

26:08.186 --> 26:13.272
That if we keep that behavior out in front of them, eventually the Holy Spirit will convict their heart and things are gonna change.

26:15.434 --> 26:18.317
You can only control your half of the equation.

26:18.398 --> 26:20.300
You can't make them do it, but you can do it yourself.

26:21.801 --> 26:27.628
I told you this wasn't easy, but it is something that's critical for good, strong, healthy marriages.

26:28.949 --> 26:33.554
Honor, respect, be the initiator of that.

26:34.946 --> 26:36.589
Now, I already know I can see your faces.

26:36.709 --> 26:38.612
I know you're looking at me like this guy is out of touch.

26:38.692 --> 26:39.012
I'm not.

26:39.032 --> 26:39.794
I'm just reading scripture.

26:40.114 --> 26:40.955
You know where I'm coming from.

26:41.336 --> 26:41.997
I know this though.

26:42.237 --> 26:43.840
And I want to share something with you.

26:44.120 --> 26:46.684
When this gets really hard to do, you're saying, you don't work for my boss.

26:46.744 --> 26:47.105
I get it.

26:47.425 --> 26:48.467
You're not married to my wife.

26:48.607 --> 26:49.368
I understand that.

26:51.031 --> 26:54.596
If you can't respect the person, if you struggle respecting the person, you know what I'm going to say?

26:54.637 --> 26:55.818
Respect the position.

26:55.858 --> 26:56.680
Fill that in if you would.

26:56.920 --> 26:58.162
Honor the position.

26:59.074 --> 27:00.997
Pray for the position, pray for that person.

27:01.217 --> 27:02.219
It's the best thing you can do.

27:02.439 --> 27:05.083
It's really hard to be bitter and resentful towards someone.

27:05.464 --> 27:11.433
The government, your boss, your spouse, your parents, it's really hard to be that way when you're praying that God would bless them.

27:14.658 --> 27:15.359
That's the prayer.

27:16.220 --> 27:19.184
Too many of us waste our prayer time getting together and going, you know what?

27:19.224 --> 27:20.346
God, change them.

27:22.209 --> 27:23.211
The right prayer is God.

27:23.231 --> 27:24.152
I want to honor them.

27:24.392 --> 27:25.354
God, change me.

27:27.537 --> 27:28.178
Change me.

27:28.642 --> 27:30.505
God bless them, and what starts to happen?

27:30.565 --> 27:32.888
We start praying blessings over these people that struggle with.

27:34.651 --> 27:37.475
God starts changing men, I change them, but God's certainly gonna change your heart.

27:39.178 --> 27:42.723
It's critical to understand that's the level of respect and honor that God wants.

27:42.743 --> 27:46.008
So, we have to respect God, others, we've mentioned a few things.

27:46.228 --> 27:46.809
Here's one more.

27:47.069 --> 27:49.273
We need to respect those that are in the world around me.

27:50.715 --> 27:52.738
Those that are in the world around me.

27:52.758 --> 27:53.919
This is everybody else, okay?

27:53.939 --> 27:58.386
This is the guy who does your oil change, the barista at Starbucks,

27:58.530 --> 28:08.343
The lady in the car that's texting next to you, that's drifting over and drifting over and drifting over and not paying attention to the road and you're beefing the horn and you're mad as a hornet and you're like, move over and you got all kinds of choice words.

28:08.363 --> 28:09.344
You tell them they're number one.

28:10.085 --> 28:11.267
Respect them too.

28:11.747 --> 28:13.129
This is everybody else, okay?

28:13.149 --> 28:14.932
Everybody that wasn't included in the first two groups.

28:15.192 --> 28:18.777
The world around you, look at the Bible says, I love this scripture, Romans 12, 10.

28:20.038 --> 28:22.061
Paul says, love one another.

28:22.121 --> 28:23.523
Doesn't say love the people you like.

28:23.743 --> 28:25.906
Doesn't say love the people that are nice to you, does it?

28:26.338 --> 28:29.082
It says, love one another, everybody with brotherly affection.

28:31.145 --> 28:32.888
This is a big next phrase, if you would circle it.

28:33.148 --> 28:35.752
Outdo one another in showing honor.

28:35.953 --> 28:38.537
Not just honor and respect, but more than they're doing it.

28:40.680 --> 28:42.202
Honor and respect more than they are.

28:42.222 --> 28:44.726
Honor and respect, why?

28:44.967 --> 28:46.108
Because Jesus lived this way.

28:46.128 --> 28:47.350
Think about how Jesus was treated.

28:48.692 --> 28:50.175
Jesus was, they tried to kill him.

28:50.215 --> 28:51.677
They tried to run him out of town.

28:51.937 --> 28:52.979
And eventually they crucified him.

28:52.999 --> 28:54.962
And you know how Jesus dealt with all that dishonor?

28:55.746 --> 28:56.787
He respected everybody.

28:57.188 --> 28:58.930
He loved him.

28:58.950 --> 29:01.713
He helped him anyway.

29:01.733 --> 29:04.577
That's why we need to honor everyone else because Jesus did it.

29:04.617 --> 29:08.882
And the second reason is because the Bible tells us our goal is to become more like him.

29:10.104 --> 29:14.730
If we're gonna become more like Christ, we wanna grow in our faith, we need to honor people the way Jesus did it.

29:16.592 --> 29:17.854
I'm not gonna lie to you, this is hard.

29:19.516 --> 29:20.817
This is tough, I know.

29:22.039 --> 29:22.740
I put this in your notes.

29:22.980 --> 29:24.562
Honor is to be given freely

29:25.250 --> 29:27.313
not positioned for expectantly.

29:28.415 --> 29:31.520
Honors to be given freely, not positioned for expectantly.

29:31.580 --> 29:33.483
Luke 14, eight, stay with me here.

29:33.503 --> 29:35.626
This verse doesn't seem like it fits, but it perfectly fits.

29:37.129 --> 29:44.480
When someone invites you to a wedding feast, do not take the place of honor for a person more distinguished than you might have been invited.

29:46.844 --> 29:47.024
Right?

29:48.286 --> 29:49.408
Don't sit at the head of the table.

29:52.273 --> 29:53.074
I deserve this.

29:54.754 --> 29:55.675
I'm older than they are.

29:56.076 --> 29:57.037
I'm smarter than they are.

29:58.218 --> 29:59.220
I have more money than they do.

30:01.202 --> 30:02.023
I deserve this honor.

30:03.345 --> 30:04.947
No.

30:04.967 --> 30:05.968
That's not what Scripture says.

30:06.769 --> 30:08.151
Don't sit at the head of the table.

30:08.171 --> 30:09.072
Don't sit on the throne.

30:09.913 --> 30:11.636
Where we belong is right here at the foot.

30:14.600 --> 30:22.770
Because if you're a Christ follower, what we tend to forget is that all of us, you and I, we're just servants.

30:25.794 --> 30:28.858
Anytime you see yourself higher than that, it's pride.

30:30.861 --> 30:31.982
All of us serve the king.

30:33.104 --> 30:35.167
All of us do honor to other people.

30:35.327 --> 30:37.790
All of us sit here at the foot, not at the head.

30:39.232 --> 30:39.873
That's not the goal.

30:41.876 --> 30:44.179
All of us, and we've got to get a hold of that.

30:47.443 --> 30:48.465
Please write this down someplace.

30:48.485 --> 30:51.529
I didn't make this a blank, but this is the key here.

30:52.811 --> 30:55.314
Honor should be given, not earned.

30:58.658 --> 31:00.921
That is a paradigm shifting way of thinking.

31:01.281 --> 31:04.004
Honor should be given, not earned, because you've heard your whole life.

31:04.205 --> 31:08.990
When they start respecting me, you don't give respect, people earn it, right?

31:09.010 --> 31:10.853
You've heard that your whole life, I heard it my whole life too.

31:11.113 --> 31:12.134
Scripture says otherwise.

31:12.354 --> 31:13.336
You give it first.

31:15.318 --> 31:16.059
That's what Jesus did.

31:19.243 --> 31:25.330
And every inch of you, trust me, I wrote that down and I just sat there and went, really God, do I really have to say that out loud?

31:26.338 --> 31:27.640
It's so counter-cultural.

31:27.800 --> 31:28.961
It's such a different way of thinking.

31:29.181 --> 31:30.122
I'm supposed to honor first.

31:30.483 --> 31:32.165
They have to earn my respect.

31:32.185 --> 31:32.405
No.

31:34.147 --> 31:36.690
Scripture tells us to honor and respect them because you know why?

31:37.091 --> 31:38.132
Jesus died for them too.

31:40.274 --> 31:41.095
They matter to Him.

31:42.878 --> 31:43.478
So how do I do it?

31:44.359 --> 31:45.581
I put a few ideas in your outline.

31:45.601 --> 31:46.862
Here's the first way we can honor someone.

31:47.042 --> 31:48.504
We can encourage them.

31:48.524 --> 31:50.066
How many in the room today like encouragement?

31:50.306 --> 31:50.827
Raise your hand.

31:52.028 --> 31:52.809
How many of you are awake?

31:52.869 --> 31:53.490
Raise your hand.

31:54.658 --> 31:54.938
Good.

31:54.999 --> 31:55.259
All right.

31:55.479 --> 31:56.481
I got you through the tough stuff.

31:56.501 --> 31:57.482
This gets more upbeat.

31:58.063 --> 31:58.864
But man, it's important.

31:59.445 --> 31:59.926
Encouragement.

32:00.126 --> 32:01.428
We love encouragement, don't we?

32:02.009 --> 32:03.391
You guys, again, you look fantastic.

32:03.551 --> 32:04.553
You guys especially up here.

32:04.913 --> 32:05.734
Thanks for sitting up close.

32:05.935 --> 32:06.375
Awesome.

32:06.395 --> 32:08.198
All of our campuses, you guys in Pensacola, awesome.

32:08.779 --> 32:09.620
We love encouragement.

32:10.481 --> 32:13.406
Encouragement is great, but far too many times we don't give it.

32:13.586 --> 32:14.567
We figure they already know.

32:15.409 --> 32:19.855
I do a lot of funerals to people that come up and say, pastor, I'd like to have five more minutes with the deceased.

32:20.436 --> 32:20.977
And I say, why?

32:20.997 --> 32:23.641
They say, because I really like to let them know how I felt.

32:23.661 --> 32:24.562
I want to encourage them.

32:24.994 --> 32:28.299
If you feel something about somebody and you want to encourage them, tell them today.

32:29.280 --> 32:33.386
Tell them now, honor and respect them, not right now because you're still listening.

32:33.587 --> 32:36.531
But when this is done, then tell them it's important.

32:36.591 --> 32:38.134
Keep a short account with encouragement.

32:38.975 --> 32:40.557
It's a great way to show respect and honor.

32:41.519 --> 32:41.939
It's a great way.

32:41.959 --> 32:43.201
Here's another way is to help them.

32:44.102 --> 32:45.545
You know how you can help some people the most?

32:46.366 --> 32:47.467
Step into a situation.

32:47.487 --> 32:48.990
Let's say their life is kind of falling apart.

32:49.190 --> 32:54.578
When you step in, when everybody else is stepping out, that's such a great sign of respect.

32:55.394 --> 32:58.777
They're going through a relationship crisis or an economic crisis or a spiritual crisis.

32:58.997 --> 33:01.300
And it gets really hard and everybody wants to dip out and bail.

33:01.600 --> 33:03.081
You step in and say, what can I do?

33:03.161 --> 33:03.662
I'm here to help.

33:04.463 --> 33:05.003
Whatever it is.

33:05.323 --> 33:07.005
What a great way to show respect to someone.

33:07.866 --> 33:09.327
So we want to encourage, we want to help.

33:09.347 --> 33:09.848
Here's a third.

33:10.248 --> 33:10.889
Sacrifice.

33:10.929 --> 33:11.589
Please fill that in.

33:12.670 --> 33:13.191
Sacrifice.

33:13.231 --> 33:15.733
Sometimes honoring someone costs you something.

33:16.214 --> 33:18.115
It doesn't necessarily mean monetarily.

33:18.436 --> 33:25.202
Sacrifice could be you're sacrificing your agenda for them.

33:26.018 --> 33:29.883
If you've forgotten an argument with somebody, sometimes sacrifice and honor simply means this.

33:29.983 --> 33:35.249
Even if you think that you're right, you stop the argument because you value the relationship more than being right.

33:37.292 --> 33:37.852
That's honor.

33:38.934 --> 33:39.654
That's respect.

33:40.555 --> 33:41.196
That's important.

33:41.497 --> 33:43.399
So we need to just do the sacrifice thing.

33:43.439 --> 33:45.341
I mean, that was Jesus's way of honoring the world.

33:45.381 --> 33:46.783
He gave up everything for us.

33:48.485 --> 33:48.825
Everything.

33:49.867 --> 33:50.467
How about the next one?

33:50.547 --> 33:51.008
Defend.

33:52.049 --> 33:52.690
Defend.

33:53.154 --> 33:55.418
You ever had a friend speak well of you when you weren't even there?

33:55.518 --> 33:57.401
You find out later on, they talk so highly of you.

33:58.102 --> 34:02.370
You know, I love to think that somebody somewhere has defended me when I wasn't even there.

34:02.390 --> 34:04.233
Like my name came up and they started bashing me.

34:04.453 --> 34:07.799
And one of my friends stood up for me and said, you know what, that Brian, he's not as bad as you think he is.

34:08.881 --> 34:10.103
And they defend my reputation.

34:10.163 --> 34:10.744
I love that.

34:11.064 --> 34:11.986
I love to think that.

34:12.610 --> 34:16.676
Or, you know, maybe it's your work and they send all the guys stand around the water cooler.

34:16.696 --> 34:17.557
I don't think do that anymore.

34:17.618 --> 34:20.322
But all the guys are standing around talking about how nasty their wives are.

34:20.562 --> 34:23.306
And you stand up for your wife and you say, no, no, no, guys, this is, no.

34:24.969 --> 34:25.429
That's honor.

34:27.653 --> 34:29.195
That again, it's counter-cultural.

34:29.255 --> 34:29.756
It's different.

34:29.876 --> 34:31.278
But that's what respect looks like.

34:31.358 --> 34:31.819
Defense.

34:32.520 --> 34:33.441
Standing up for somebody.

34:33.602 --> 34:34.543
The next one is listening.

34:35.645 --> 34:35.965
Listening.

34:35.985 --> 34:38.168
You can always tell good listeners because they have a lot of what?

34:38.289 --> 34:39.250
They have a lot of friends.

34:40.322 --> 34:42.765
Everybody wants to talk and fix very few want to listen.

34:42.805 --> 34:52.715
Sometimes the greatest way to honor somebody is to stop your life and just be an open ear, not for gossip, but to hear them out, to let them use you as a sounding board.

34:52.735 --> 34:55.478
And one last one, we're gonna dig into this one next week.

34:55.498 --> 34:58.541
It's loyalty, be loyal, be loyal.

34:59.102 --> 35:01.064
If someone else makes a decision, you defend it.

35:02.205 --> 35:06.930
Instead of looking for the grass is always greener, going over there and doing something else, water the grass that you're on.

35:07.362 --> 35:08.223
Stay put.

35:08.243 --> 35:08.944
Defend people.

35:08.964 --> 35:10.926
Stand shoulder to shoulder when the odds aren't good.

35:12.247 --> 35:13.869
We're gonna talk a lot more about that next week.

35:13.909 --> 35:17.212
Loyalty's important, but loyalty's a great way to honor somebody.

35:18.053 --> 35:18.794
And there's so many more.

35:18.814 --> 35:23.419
These are just a few ideas as we figure out a way to honor God and other people.

35:23.519 --> 35:26.482
Now in a wrap up our time today with sharing the ultimate act of honor.

35:26.502 --> 35:32.448
Now this is something that, when I read through scripture, other than the crucifixion itself, it's so inspiring.

35:33.269 --> 35:34.450
Jesus himself did it in.

35:34.914 --> 35:40.782
Right before Jesus went to the cross, you probably read this story if you haven't, I advise you to do it, it's in Matthew, it's in all the gospels really.

35:41.943 --> 35:44.407
Jesus before he goes to the cross has one final meal with his men.

35:45.748 --> 35:47.351
Maybe you've seen it referred to as the Last Supper.

35:49.413 --> 35:53.819
And he knows that one of those men is gonna betray him to the Roman authorities and he's gonna be dragged away and crucified.

35:54.720 --> 36:01.449
So the night before that happens, Jesus gathers his men in the room and he takes a basin filled with water.

36:01.469 --> 36:04.914
Now I don't know if it looked like this one or not, but just for the sake of illustration,

36:05.826 --> 36:11.935
Jesus grabbed a basin and a towel, and he went one by one to all of his men and washed their feet.

36:13.878 --> 36:17.022
Now back then, they didn't wear closed shoes, so those feet were pretty grimy.

36:17.824 --> 36:22.570
They walked around in sandals for the dust and dirt from all the places these men had walked throughout many days, probably.

36:23.472 --> 36:33.266
Jesus, the King of Kings, the Lord of Lords, the Alpha, the Omega, the creator of every single person around that table, he got down on his hands and his knees, and he washed their feet.

36:35.266 --> 36:38.970
And I think to myself, what an incredible act of honor.

36:40.932 --> 36:48.079
Because Jesus not only washed the feet of the 11 men that were on his side still, he washed the feet of his betrayer.

36:50.762 --> 36:51.643
What an act of love.

36:53.845 --> 36:54.947
It revealed Jesus' heart.

36:57.329 --> 36:58.150
He loved those guys.

36:59.551 --> 37:02.034
And by washing their feet, he reminded them they had value.

37:04.066 --> 37:08.832
And he also did it because he wants all of us to treat each other the same way.

37:11.055 --> 37:21.748
Because it's not about the throne and how many likes you get on Instagram, how many Facebook things, I don't know what you call them anymore, likes, thumbs ups, whatever.

37:23.189 --> 37:23.910
It's not about that.

37:25.793 --> 37:33.522
It's about sacrifice, commitment, love, encouragement, defense,

37:33.890 --> 37:35.872
protection of others.

37:37.554 --> 37:48.706
And there's a scripture, John 13, after Jesus was done washing their feet, look what he says, he says, and since I, your Lord and teacher, have washed your feet, you ought to wash each other's feet, underline that if you would.

37:49.367 --> 37:51.869
I've given you an example, circle example to follow.

37:52.130 --> 37:57.315
Do as I have done to you, and now that you know these things, God will bless you for doing them.

37:57.655 --> 38:00.018
I want to tell you, if you start to honor people like this,

38:00.290 --> 38:02.193
and sacrifice them and put them above yourself.

38:02.293 --> 38:04.196
People are going to look at you funny like, what are you doing?

38:07.520 --> 38:10.164
You're encouraging them.

38:10.424 --> 38:11.806
You're defending them.

38:12.047 --> 38:13.068
You're protecting them.

38:13.449 --> 38:14.430
You're honoring them.

38:14.470 --> 38:16.212
Yeah.

38:17.735 --> 38:19.577
Because I'm following not the example of the world.

38:19.637 --> 38:20.519
I'm following the example.

38:21.219 --> 38:21.860
Jesus Christ.

38:23.322 --> 38:24.825
He's the only one worthy of that throne.

38:27.568 --> 38:28.690
That is why I honor.

38:30.530 --> 38:31.771
because Jesus first honored us.

38:33.854 --> 38:37.178
And it brings him great joy when we do this for other people.

38:38.739 --> 38:39.500
I put this in your notes.

38:41.422 --> 38:48.631
We worship God, which leads to us honoring others, which leads to us as the Scripture just told us that we're blessed when we do it.

38:51.113 --> 38:52.855
Now, I want to challenge your church this week.

38:54.357 --> 38:58.802
One of these things that I mentioned to you hopefully has knocked on the door of your heart.

39:00.034 --> 39:06.261
Whether it be your boss, maybe it's God's house, your kids, the government.

39:06.301 --> 39:12.708
I don't know which one, but I want to challenge you this week to start putting this into practice.

39:12.728 --> 39:17.934
Because time after time in Scripture, when we're obedient in this area of our lives, God says, I will bless you for that.

39:19.675 --> 39:23.079
And I don't know about you, but I certainly could use more blessing in my life.

39:24.020 --> 39:29.426
I promise, if we can start doing this regularly, what's going to happen is every relationship in your life is going to change.

39:30.338 --> 39:35.062
God will be glorified and all of us will be blessed as a result.

39:35.783 --> 39:40.828
I hope and my prayer from the bottom of my heart is I pray that something you could subscribe to too.

39:42.289 --> 39:45.072
Let's pray together.

39:45.092 --> 39:46.393
God, we love you, we thank you.

39:46.814 --> 39:53.380
Father, I know there's a lot of things in your word that we read them and Father, we wrestle with them.

39:55.882 --> 39:59.986
We think, Father, that doesn't necessarily apply to me or that

40:00.098 --> 40:03.764
Maybe the Bible is out of touch, or that God would understand if I didn't.

40:05.947 --> 40:08.651
Father, I would ask that that's what somebody's wrestling with right now.

40:08.691 --> 40:16.363
Just like I have done all week long, the Father would open their eyes to a new way of treating others.

40:16.383 --> 40:19.067
Sacrifice, love, commitment, encouragement.

40:19.227 --> 40:21.470
God just reveals so much about where we are with you.

40:23.493 --> 40:29.202
Help us start walking forward in this area, honoring people, not judging them, hugging,

40:29.378 --> 40:30.219
Not pushing away.

40:30.279 --> 40:34.886
It's God we know that when we do those things, we honor you.

40:36.028 --> 40:42.117
Thank you for the tremendous example, washing those men's feet, going to the cross on our behalf.

40:42.177 --> 40:44.881
Help us, Father, follow in your footsteps.

40:46.283 --> 40:47.565
And all glory will go to you.

40:48.586 --> 40:49.748
It's a Christ name that I pray.

40:51.030 --> 40:51.350
Amen.

40:51.851 --> 40:52.071
Amen.

40:52.091 --> 40:53.874
Let's give God a hand today if you would.

